We show that every finite volume hyperbolic manifold of dimension greater or
equal to 3 is stable under rescaled Ricci flow, i.e. that every small
perturbation of the hyperbolic metric flows back to the hyperbolic metric
again. Note that we do not need to make any decay assumptions on this
perturbation.
  It will turn out that the main difficulty in the proof comes from a weak
stability of the cusps which has to do with infinitesimal cusp deformations. We
will overcome this weak stability by using a new analytical method developed by
Koch and Lamm.